<topic id="folding-in-css-stylesheets">
  <title>Folding in CSS Stylesheets</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>CSS stylesheets<indexterm>Folding</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>In a large CSS stylesheet document, some styles can be collapsed so that only the styles that
      are needed remain in focus. The same <xref href="folding-of-the-xml-elements.dita">folding
        features available for XML documents</xref> are also available in CSS stylesheets.<note><ph
          conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/selecting-blocks"/></note></p>
  </body>
